Phase 7 is fully implemented. Here's a summary of what was done:

---

## Phase 7 — Complete

### Phase 7.1 — Permission-Guarded Routes
- **`AuthUser` & `JwtPayload`** — extended with `permissions?: string[]`
- **`use-login.ts`** — now decodes `permissions` from JWT and stores in auth store
- **`ROUTES.FORBIDDEN`** — added `/forbidden` constant; `ForbiddenPage` registered in router under `AuthGuard`
- **`permission-guard.tsx`** — accepts `requiredPermissions` (any-match by default, all-match with `requireAll=true`); reads `user.permissions` from Zustand auth store; logs `FORBIDDEN_ROUTE_ACCESS_ATTEMPT` with `userId` and `path`; redirects to `/forbidden`
- **Router** — `/admin/roles` and `/admin/roles/:roleId` wrapped in `PermissionGuard` requiring any of `['role:create', 'role:update', 'role:delete']`

### Phase 7.2 — Permission-Aware UI Rendering
- **`useRolePermissions`** — new hook deriving 5 boolean flags (`canCreateRole`, `canUpdateRole`, `canDeleteRole`, `canGrantPermission`, `canRevokePermission`) from the auth store; no API calls
- **`RolesPage`** — "New Role" button visible only when `canCreateRole`
- **`RoleDetailPage`** — "Edit Role" only when `canUpdateRole`; "Delete Role" only when `canDeleteRole` (still `aria-disabled`+tooltip for system roles)
- **`RolePermissionsPanel`** — "Assign Permission" only when `canGrantPermission`; "Remove" per item only when `canRevokePermission`
- **`UserRolesPanel`** — "Assign Role" and "Remove" only when `canUpdateRole`

### Tests
- 8 new `PermissionGuard` unit tests
- 13 new `useRolePermissions` unit tests  
- 21 new integration tests for permission-aware UI across 4 component test files
- All existing tests updated with auth store setup (`beforeEach`/`afterEach`)
- **323 tests pass across 38 test files** (was 281/36)
